{
  "message": "As the President of Saguaro Strikers, I would like to extend a warm welcome to all members as we embark on our journey into the world of STEM. Here, we can explore creativity and curiosity while working on innovative projects and collaborating as a team.\n\nOur club is a space for individuals to engage with science, technology, engineering, and math, regardless of their prior experience. Whether you are launching rockets, programming robots, or simply curious about how things operate, you will find a supportive environment that encourages curiosity and learning. Each member brings their own unique background and perspective, which is extremely valuable to our group. I encourage everyone to share their ideas and ask questions, as collaboration often leads to the best outcomes. We have a variety of activities planned, including hands-on rocket launches, robotics challenges, and community STEM initiatives and I hope each of you takes the opportunity to participate. If you need assistance, don’t hesitate to reach out; we're here to learn from one another. As we move forward this year, let's focus on getting locked and loaded for the various robotics and rocketry competitions we might participate in. We will encounter challenges along the way, but remember that these experiences provide very valuable lessons for our futures.\nWe invite you to join us as we explore new possibilities within the world of STEM. Regardless of your current skill level, our club provides a unique opportunity to develop technical abilities, collaborate with peers, and contribute to innovative projects. By participating, you will gain access to hands-on workshops and mentorship that will help you grow both as a student and a future professional. I look forward to seeing what we can achieve together this year and the unique ideas you will bring to our team. Your contributions will be essential as we prepare for upcoming competitions and community events. Furthermore, we believe that the skills learned here, such as problem-solving and critical thinking in times of high pressure, will be beneficial in all areas of our academic lives. I am eager to see how our collective efforts will shape the club's journey in the coming years.",
  "name": "Jyotishka Roy",
  "title": "Mission Director",
  "image": "/uploads/mission-director/HLHdiynMUKiA.png"
}

